	 ICL to start 				 on Nov. 30						
	 Chennai: The Indian Cricket League (ICL) announced that the inaugural edition of its Twenty20 championship will be held from November 30-December 16 in Chandigarh. The final will be played on December 16.						
	 Ashraf to stay 3 more years						
	 Faisalabad: Pakistan President Pervez Musharraf has retained Dr Nasim Ashraf as chairman of the PCB for the next three years. A notification was issued to this effect from the President rsquo;s secretariat on Tuesday. The President is also the chief patron of the PCB.						
	 Pak request						
	 Faisalabad: Pakistan has asked the ICC to move next year rsquo;s Champions Trophy to October because it coincides with the Muslim holy month of Ramazan. Shafqat Naghmi, the PCB rsquo;s chief operating officer, said he hoped the dates could be moved to avoid the month-long fast and minimise the risk of a decline in ticket sales.						
	 Arjuna wish						
	 Melbourne: Former Sri Lanka captain Arjuna Ranatunga had advised Muttiah Muralidharan not to tour Australia as the home crowd would be at its hostile worst with the off-spinner preparing to overtake Shane Warne as Test cricket rsquo;s wicket-taker.
 ldquo;I told him I wished he wasn rsquo;t touring Australia because of the amount of trouble he has had, rdquo; Ranatunga was quoted as saying in a paper. The legendary off-spinner, however, left with the squad on Tuesday.						
